</b></p>
<p><b>24</b>/&#8230;<b> Civil society space: creating and maintaining, in law and in 
practice, a safe and enabling environment 
</b></p>
<p>Paragraph 6 <i>should read 
</i></p>
<p><i>Emphasizes</i> the essential role of civil society in subregional, regional and 
international organizations, including in support of the organizations&#8217; work, and in sharing 
experience and expertise through participation in meetings, in accordance with relevant 
rules and modalities for participation in meetings and activities of all the above-mentioned 
organizations, including Economic and Social Council resolution 1996/31 of 25 July 1996 
and other decisions relevant to the United Nations,   
</p>
